\begin_layout Standard
Commodity value chains play a central role in structural transformation.
 Recently, value chains studies have started looking at inclusiveness, as
 some argue that especially high value global supply chains my benefit only
 certain groups in society.
 Available evidence shows that this does not always appears to be the case
 
